<DOC>
<DOCNO>36374_1</DOCNO>
<TEXT>70 Virginis

</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>36374_2</DOCNO>
<TEXT>70 Virginis (abbreviated 70 Vir) is the Flamsteed designation of a yellow dwarf star approximately 59 light-years away in the constellation Virgo. It is rather unusually bright for its spectral type and may be just starting to evolve into the subgiant phase.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>36374_3</DOCNO>
<TEXT>In 1996, 70 Virginis was discovered to have an extrasolar planet in orbit around it. There is also a dust disc with a maximum temperature of 153 K located at a minimum distance of 3.4 AU from the star.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
